Nollywood actress, Funke Akindele, has expressed concern over children enrolled in Dowen College, despite the death of 12-year-old Sylvester Oromoni. The chairman of the school board and members had on Friday stepped down. The school noted that due to the unfortunate incident, they are reviewing some of their policies to ensure better oversight functions within the school. Gani Adams To Nigerians In Diaspora: Shun Negative News, Develop… Jim Iyke Opens Up On Why He Doesn’t Follow Anyone On… Reacting to this development Funke via her Instagram story, shared a picture of the school and questioned if parents of wards attending the school have withdrawn their wards. She wrote, “I hope all parents have withdrawn their children from the school. “I’m so worried for children in boarding schools. A lot goes on there.”